{
  "texts": [
    "Brahmachary et al.",
    "propose the Language-model-based Evolutionary Optimizer (LEO) for population-based EAs, which focuses on the balance between exploration and exploitation [33].",
    "LEO divides the solution set into exploration and exploitation pools.",
    "It utilizes LLMs to generate new solutions for the two pools separately based on different prompts.",
    "Then, LEO uses an elitism selection strategy to guide the evolutionary direction, which imports the solutions with the minimum objective function values from the exploration pool into the exploitation pool, while removing solutions with the maximum objective function values from the exploitation pool."
  ]
}